Re: A short description about myself
by chikara » Wed 03.31.2010 10:01 pm Nakagawa Izumi wrote:...... I was trying to say I was in the 10nth grade ....10級Nakagawa Izumi wrote:...... is separating words using multiple "to" particles okay in Japanese? .....You are not separating words but using the equivalent of "and" which is a conjunction. While in English it is common to replace all but the ultimate "and" with a comma this is not the same in Japanese.
Don't complain to me that people kick you when you're down. It's your own fault for lying there
