Re: A short description about myself
by Kakads » Thu 04.01.2010 5:20 am Nakagawa Izumi wrote:3.The polite verb forms (+masu) are not necessary in this caseWhen using koto to turn a verb into a noun phrase, the verb should be in the dictionary form. As verbs go at the end of the setence, you would need to turn them into noun phrases to fit them into one sentence. Think of the first sentence as 'My hobby is the thing(koto) of watching(miru) anime'.
